gomodel:SYNGO_2818  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Expression of NOS1AP-L or NOS1AP-S in COS-7 cells decreases F-actin\"\nFig.2: \"Effects of NOS1AP-L or NOS1AP-S overexpression on protrusion index and F-actin\"\nFig.3: \"NOS1AP-S decreases total Rac1 and cofilin protein expression in HEK293T cells\"\nFig.4: \"NOS1AP-L and NOS1AP-S associate with F-actin and promote actin polymerization\"\nFig.5: \"NOS1AP-L alter spine number and morphology.\"\nFig.6: \"NOS1AP-S alter spine number and morphology\"\nFig.7: \"NOS1AP-S increases synaptic strength, while NOS1AP-L decreases synaptic strength\". Experimental description: - \"Neuronal cultures were plated from cortices of rat embryos at 18 days gestation...\"\n- \"Whole cell patch-clamp recordings were made on the soma of cortical neurons....\"\n- Overexpressed NOS1AP is of human species: \" cDNAs encoding long and short isoforms of human NOS1AP (NOS1AP-L and NOS1AP-S), NOS1AP-S-1-197 (NOS1AP-S-ΔPDZ), NOS1AP-L-214-end (NOS1AP-L-ΔPTB), NOS1AP-L-1-487 (NOS1AP-L-ΔPDZ), and NOS1AP-L-181-307 (NOS1AP-M) were sub cloned into pCAG-GFP as described previously (Carrel et al., 2009).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2818" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

